##I am stranded in Jingzhou, a hard-hit city 100km from Wuhan

Micro-signal Xinminzhoukan

Function description, depth and angle —— this is what we can do.

Peripheral Vision

DECLUTTER | Bing Chen

Peripheral Vision

DECLUTTER | Bing Chen

On January 18, the first day of my son's winter vacation, my family drove 14 hours back to my birthplace -- Luoshan town of Honghu, Hubei Province (Jingzhou) . Honghu, named for Hong Lake, the largest lake on our side, is a county-level city with a registered population of just over 930,000, about 100 kilometers from Wuhan.

The outbreak in Hubei had not yet been reported, and if we had known it was that serious, we would not have come back.

Back home, the epidemic is getting worse by the day. On the night of January 23, the Honghu new crown pneumonia epidemic prevention and control headquarters issued a No. 6 order, fully activating the secondary response to public health emergencies, implementing traffic control, suspending the city's public transport, and combining the three checks at the entrance of the highway, cancel the gathering. All our family dinners and New Year's greetings have been cancelled.

On January 25, the first day of the Lunar New Year, Honghu issued the 12th order: from January 25 at 10:00 on the city road access closed to traffic, except for special vehicles.

Which means Hong Lake is closed.

At present, my family of three plus my parents five people living together for more than 20 days. Because we are in the suburbs, about 8 kilometers away from downtown Hong Lake, plus the Spring Festival buy a lot of goods, vegetables are picked from their own fields, so basically there is no big problem to eat.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Roads in the countryside are closed, private cars are impassable, gas stations are closed, traffic between towns is closed, and there are traffic police on duty. Now, outside people can not get in, inside people can not get out, only the electric car can pass, everyone knows that the outside is dangerous, do not run around, at most go out to buy some fruit or something. The countryside is less densely populated, so it feels safer than the city.

At a critical moment, village cadres dressed in protective clothing went door-to-door and distributed face masks according to the number of people. They went door-to-door every day to take body temperature measurements. The village loudspeakers were filled with news about the epidemic every day. I think the measures are still in place, right, and there was no limit on disposable masks, so my mom went to the village clinic and bought a bag, 50 of them, which seemed to last a long time.

A new case of coronary pneumonia was confirmed in our village yesterday (February 9) , and the whole village knows about it. I asked how the news spread so quickly, they said that the epidemic prevention department immediately after the diagnosis to call the village, later confirmed that this person registered here, the family lives in the city, has not been back recently. So, for now, our village is safe.

One of the residents of the next village, who had returned from Wuhan Years Earlier, had been quarantined from thirty close contacts, and now they were coming back.

Before some people in the village Rode Electric Bikes to the next village to play cards, always feel the epidemic far away from their own, and later feel that the infection is quite terrible, do not go out to play. But it must be very boring to stay at home all day. Some people in the village still get together to play cards. I'm afraid if they catch it..

On February 9, the city issued a notice to implement a temporary pass system for residents. One household with one pass will be allowed to leave the village (community) , and one person from each household will be allowed to go out every three days on the strength of an identity card and a temporary pass, each time by the village (community) prevention and Control Checkpoint (gate) is responsible for the check, check; within the tentative scope, for business needs, but also issued a unit stamped with the official seal of proof.

In my hometown, the front and back of the House are more spacious. During the day, I accompany my son to do homework, watch TV, and when the weather is good, I sunbathe at the door, or go fishing in the river at the door for some recreation. February 10th was supposed to be the start of my company in Shanghai, but due to the complete disruption of traffic, we couldn't drive back, so we had to set up the company remotely -- as if some of the employees were back at work, control the number of employees in the district.

WE ARE DOING AUTO-RELATED PARTS R & D Verification Related testing equipment, the impact of the epidemic on the company is still quite large, orders are not delivered on time, not a penny less labor costs, I am in financial communication, look at the 28 new Shanghai can help offset what costs, I believe the government can help us small and micro enterprises to tide over the difficulties.

In any case, I can still live a half-day of leisure, a "picking Ju Dong Li, leisurely see Nanshan" new village life, so it is not too anxious, in fact, anxiety is useless.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
I don't know how much longer we're GONNA be locked down, watching the news every day, feeling that things are getting better in Jingzhou, that the authorities are still responsible. Hang in there. We're GONNA beat this.

As of 2400 hours on February 9,2020, a total of 1,045 cases of COVID-19 pneumonia have been reported in Jingzhou, Hubei Province, with the incidence rate behind Wuhan, Xiaogan, Huanggang and Suizhou. At about 10:00 am on January 27, Wang Mou, the first severe case of COVID-19 pneumonia in Jingzhou, was discharged from the city chest hospital. The 46-year-old male patient, surnamed Wang, who had been working as a live seafood carrier in south China Seafood City, Wuhan, was referred to the outpatient department of Jingzhou Chest Hospital on January 7 and was transferred to an isolation ward for symptomatic and supportive treatment. "It's not a terrible disease, " said Wang, who was cured. "If you cooperate with doctors, everything will be fine. " At 2:17 a.m. on January 28, the Hainan medical team arrived in Jingzhou, this is the first medical team to fly to Jingzhou to fight COVID-19 pneumonia. The Hainan medical team consisted of 147 people, including 145 medical workers from 12 second-class hospitals in Hainan Province, who came from the Department of Suction, the Department of First Aid, the Department of Nursing and so on. The medical staff were divided into 11 groups of about 15 people in each group, in Jingzhou City, five teams of medical staff are mainly responsible for the treatment of ordinary patients. Six other teams of medical staff were sent to the front lines of six counties and cities in Jingzhou to treat patients with severe illnesses.
